  "response_text": "Against a plain white studio background, a tall, rounded inflatable punching-bag figure stands on the left. It depicts the bald, smiling Mr. Clean mascot in a tight white outfit, arms crossed, with a blue outline or backing around him. From the right, an adult Black woman with long braids walks in confidently. She wears an olive-green shirt and pants with a dark patterned vest, and carries a bright magenta shoulder bag. In one hand she holds an amber-orange bottle with a green label reading “Pine-Sol.” She stops beside the Mr. Clean figure, looks him over, and reaches toward his face as if giving him a small tap or pinch near the ear, while keeping the Pine-Sol bottle visible.\n\nShe then faces forward and raises the Pine-Sol bottle near her shoulder, presenting it clearly. The bottle has a yellow cap and bold yellow “Pine-Sol” lettering on a green label, with amber liquid inside. The Mr. Clean figure remains beside her, still upright and smiling with crossed arms, while she appears to speak directly to the viewer.\n\nThe scene shifts to a bathroom setting viewed from inside or very near a white bathtub or sink. Chrome faucet handles and a shiny spout are on the right, a small yellow rubber duck sits near the center, and a wire bath caddy with colorful items hangs on the left. The woman leans over the rim from above, holding the Pine-Sol bottle. Small white text appears along the bottom: “Full strength based on lab tests.” She reaches into the bath caddy, takes out a bright green sponge, and brings it down to the white surface.\n\nA close view shows her hand pressing the green sponge against a grayish, cloudy patch of bathroom scum near the chrome drain area. She scrubs across the surface. As the sponge moves, the dull gray area gives way to a bright, clean white patch, with the chrome fixtures nearby reflecting light. The same small on-screen text about full strength and lab tests remains along the bottom during the scrubbing demonstration.\n\nBack against the white background, the woman is shown close up holding an open Pine-Sol bottle beside her face. The amber liquid is visible through the neck of the bottle, and the green label with large yellow letters is partly in view. She looks directly forward, then slightly to the side, with expressive raised brows and a knowing, persuasive expression.\n\nThe view widens again. The Mr. Clean inflatable figure now lies toppled on its side behind her to the left, no longer standing. The woman stands in front, holding the Pine-Sol bottle upright in one hand and her magenta bag over her shoulder. She gestures back toward the fallen figure with her free hand, then turns forward again, continuing to present the Pine-Sol bottle.\n\nAt the end, the products are displayed large on the left: a yellow Pine-Sol trigger spray bottle with a purple-and-white spray nozzle, and a tall amber Pine-Sol cleaner bottle with the green label and yellow cap. Above them, gray text reads, “The Power of Pine-Sol.” The woman appears much smaller to the right, standing near the oversized product display. The final image changes to bold black text reading, “The Smell of Clean.” The Pine-Sol products remain prominent on the left while the woman turns and walks away to the right, her braids swinging behind her.",
